---
import Head from '../components/Head.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
  <Head
  title="Our Books — Gloriously Unhinged"
  description="The unhinged things we wrote together — and apart." 
  />
 </head>

<body>
  <nav>
    <a href="/" class="nav-home">gloriously unhinged</a>
  </nav>

  <main>
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>Our Books</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">The unhinged things we wrote together — and apart.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- ===== TOGETHER ===== -->
    <section class="book-section">
      <h2 class="section-label">Together</h2>

      <div class="book-card">
        <div class="book-cover">
          <img src="/bbcovermockuppulp1.png" alt="Blurred Borders cover" />
        </div>
        <div class="book-info">
          <h3 class="book-title">Blurred Borders</h3>
          <p class="book-authors">Savanna Rioux & Nina Dahl</p>
          <div class="book-tags">
            <span class="tag">M/M Dark Romance</span>
            <span class="tag">Romantic Suspense</span>
            <span class="tag">Dark Comedy</span>
          </div>
          <div class="book-blurb">
            <p>
              Rafi is a reclusive billionaire who dismantles trafficking rings with
              enthusiasm and questionable methods, then rehabilitates men from bigoted
              backgrounds by making them dress as maids and do traditionally female
              chores. He has reasons. It works. But his personal life is becoming
              dangerous, his past is closing in, and his newest maid is very obviously
              a spy who isn't even subtle about it.
            </p>
            <p>
              Jude thought the army was his forever home. Medically discharged and
              uneasy at the Agency, his first encounter with true happiness is
              infiltrating what he expected to be a trafficking den — only to find an
              enjoyable breeze about his nethers, work that fulfils him, and a
              surprisingly charming kingpin who staunchly refuses to touch his very
              willing pretend-employee.
            </p>
            <p>
              Somewhere between revenge plots, emotional breakdowns, and aggressively
              domestic chaos involving matching jewelry, cats, donuts, and unsolicited
              therapy breakthroughs… they build something real.
            </p>
            <p class="book-tone">
              Messy. Violent. Unhinged.
            </p>
            <p>
              <em>Blurred Borders</em> is a dual-POV M/M dark romance about two damaged
              men who find tenderness inside brutality, healing inside absurdity, and a
              love worth burning the world down for. It is funny. It is filthy. It is
              devastating. And the maid outfit is a choice.
            </p>
          </div>
          <details class="content-warnings">
            <summary>Content warnings</summary>
            <p>
              Explicit sexual content, on-page violence, references to childhood
              sexual abuse (past), sexual assault (on-page, not romanticised), BDSM
              dynamics (both healthy and unhealthy depicted), and a hard-won HEA.
            </p>
          </details>
          <div class="book-stats">
            <div class="stat">
              <span class="stat-label">Words</span>
              <span class="stat-value">65,000</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <span class="stat-label">Pages</span>
              <span class="stat-value">229</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <span class="stat-label">Release</span>
              <span class="stat-value">Fall 2026</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="status-bar-container">
            <div class="status-label">
              <span>Revising</span>
              <span>Due May 1st</span>
            </div>
            <div class="status-track">
              <div class="status-fill" style="width: 75%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== SAVANNA ===== -->
    <section class="book-section">
      <h2 class="section-label">Savanna Rioux — Solo</h2>

      <div class="book-card">
        <div class="book-cover">
          <img src="/Inbetweentheliescover.jpeg" alt="In Between the Lies cover" />
        </div>
        <div class="book-info">
          <h3 class="book-title">In Between the Lies</h3>
          <p class="book-authors">Savanna Rioux</p>
          <div class="book-tags">
            <span class="tag">Dark Romance</span>
            <span class="tag">Urban Fantasy</span>
          </div>
          <div class="book-tropes">
            <span class="trope">Enemies to lovers</span>
            <span class="trope">She's the only one who can calm him</span>
            <span class="trope">Morally grey × morally resilient</span>
            <span class="trope">Forced proximity</span>
            <span class="trope">Slow burn with bursts of chaos</span>
          </div>
          <div class="book-blurb">
            <p>
              He was buried for three centuries. Hers was the blood that woke him.
            </p>
            <p>
              Nero is not a man — not anymore. He is something older and far more
              dangerous, a creature who has spent over a millennium as a weapon for
              those powerful enough to bind him. When Hope's blood accidentally spills
              over his coffin in the Paris catacombs, he resurfaces half-mad, half-dead,
              and entirely certain he wants nothing she's offering.
            </p>
            <p>
              Hope Masters survives on instinct, sarcasm, and sheer stubbornness. She
              didn't ask for a volatile ancient vampire tracking her back to London, a
              curse that makes her his only source of blood, or the slow, devastating
              realisation that she is falling in love with him.
            </p>
            <p>
              But Nero's past is not finished with him. His previous master is looking
              for the perfect opportunity to reclaim what's rightfully his.
            </p>
            <p class="book-tone">
              A dark paranormal romance about grief, devotion, and the kind of love
              that refuses to die.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="book-stats">
            <div class="stat">
              <span class="stat-label">Words</span>
              <span class="stat-value">~80,000</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <span class="stat-label">Pages</span>
              <span class="stat-value">~400</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <span class="stat-label">Release</span>
              <span class="stat-value">May 15th, 2026</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="status-bar-container">
            <div class="status-label">
              <span>Formatting</span>
              <span>Almost there</span>
            </div>
            <div class="status-track">
              <div class="status-fill" style="width: 92%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== NINA ===== -->
    <section class="book-section">
      <h2 class="section-label">Nina Dahl — Solo</h2>

      <div class="book-card">
        <div class="book-cover">
          <img src="/oiasbcovertemp.png" alt="Of Illusions and Stolen Bones cover" />
        </div>
        <div class="book-info">
          <h3 class="book-title">Of Illusions and Stolen Bones</h3>
          <p class="book-authors">Nina Dahl</p>
          <div class="book-tags">
            <span class="tag">Dark Fantasy Romance</span>
          </div>
          <div class="book-tropes">
            <span class="trope">Hurt/comfort</span>
            <span class="trope">Morally grey</span>
            <span class="trope">Slow burn / fast sex</span>
          </div>
          <div class="book-blurb">
            <p>
              Zanvok has a yak, a wrecked self-image, and a list of issues longer
              than his arm. Varian has a controlling family, a failing business, and
              a schedule with no space for romance.
            </p>
            <p>
              In a lawless pirate city, a broken ex-gladiator discovers he has a
              daughter — and she's in the hands of his former mentor. The search for
              her entangles him with an illusionist barely holding his family's
              business together. Together, they must stay alive, rescue the girl, and
              unravel an increasingly deadly conspiracy without losing themselves —
              or each other — in the process.
            </p>
            <p class="book-tone">
              Dark fantasy romance with teeth. Found family forged in fire, love
              built on broken foundations, and a yak.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="book-stats">
            <div class="stat">
              <span class="stat-label">Words</span>
              <span class="stat-value">~100,000</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <span class="stat-label">Pages</span>
              <span class="stat-value">~400</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <span class="stat-label">Release</span>
              <span class="stat-value">Early 2027</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="status-bar-container">
            <div class="status-label">
              <span>3rd draft revisions</span>
              <span>In progress</span>
            </div>
            <div class="status-track">
              <div class="status-fill" style="width: 45%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="back-link">
      <a href="/">← Back to home</a>
    </div>
  </main>
  <div class="lightbox" id="lightbox">
    <img id="lightbox-img" src="" alt="Enlarged cover" />
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    const lightbox = document.getElementById('lightbox');
    const lightboxImg = document.getElementById('lightbox-img');

    document.querySelectorAll('.book-cover img').forEach(img => {
      img.addEventListener('click', () => {
        lightboxImg.src = img.src;
        lightboxImg.alt = img.alt;
        lightbox.classList.add('active');
      });
    });

    lightbox.addEventListener('click', () => {
      lightbox.classList.remove('active');
    });

    document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
      if (e.key === 'Escape') lightbox.classList.remove('active');
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>

<style is:global>
  *, *::before, *::after {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  :root {
    --bg: #0d0d14;
    --surface: #151521;
    --surface-border: #2a2a3d;
    --text: #c8c8d4;
    --text-muted: #7a7a92;
    --accent: #8b7ec8;
    --accent-bright: #a594f9;
    --white: #e8e8f0;
  }

  html { font-size: 16px; scroll-behavior: smooth; }

  body {
    font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.6;
    min-height: 100vh;
    background-image: url('/purplesmoke.jpeg');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center top;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-attachment: fixed;
  }
    body::before {
    content: '';
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(13, 13, 20, 0.85);
    z-index: -1;
  }

  nav {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .nav-home {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .nav-home:hover { color: var(--accent-bright); }

  main {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem 5rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ===== SECTIONS ===== */
  .book-section {
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* ===== BOOK CARD ===== */
  .book-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--surface-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: var(--surface);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .book-cover {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 160px;
  }

  .book-cover img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 4px;
    display: block;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
    cursor: zoom-in;
    transition: transform 0.2s;
  }

  .book-cover img:hover {
    transform: scale(1.03);
  }

  /* ===== LIGHTBOX ===== */
  .lightbox {
    display: none;
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9);
    z-index: 1000;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    cursor: zoom-out;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .lightbox.active {
    display: flex;
  }

  .lightbox img {
    max-width: 90vw;
    max-height: 90vh;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
  }

  .book-info {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .book-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .book-authors {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* ===== TAGS & TROPES ===== */
  .book-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .tag {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    background: rgba(139, 126, 200, 0.15);
    color: var(--accent-bright);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .book-tropes {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .trope {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    border: 1px solid var(--surface-border);
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  /* ===== BLURB ===== */
  .book-blurb {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .book-blurb p {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .book-blurb p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .book-tone {
    color: var(--white) !important;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .book-blurb em {
    color: var(--accent-bright);
  }

  /* ===== CONTENT WARNINGS ===== */
  .content-warnings {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  .content-warnings summary {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    cursor: pointer;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 0.4rem 0;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .content-warnings summary:hover {
    color: var(--accent-bright);
  }

  .content-warnings p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding: 0.5rem 0 0;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  /* ===== STATS ===== */
  .book-stats {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--surface-border);
    border: 1px solid var(--surface-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .stat {
    flex: 1;
    background: var(--bg);
    padding: 0.75rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .stat-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .stat-value {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--white);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* ===== STATUS BAR ===== */
  .status-bar-container {
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .status-label {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .status-track {
    height: 6px;
    background: var(--bg);
    border-radius: 3px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--surface-border);
  }

  .status-fill {
    height: 100%;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent), var(--accent-bright));
    border-radius: 3px;
    transition: width 0.6s ease;
  }

  /* ===== BACK LINK ===== */
  .back-link { text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem; }

  .back-link a {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .back-link a:hover { color: var(--accent-bright); }

  /* ===== RESPONSIVE ===== */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .book-card {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .book-cover {
      width: 180px;
    }

    .book-tags, .book-tropes {
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .book-stats {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }
</style>